attributes.Long form description: The student builds the base frame of the rolling cart by screwing the leg pieces together. The student builds the upper frame by screwing the side bars together. The student builds the trays by screwing the brackets onto the trays. The student builds the wheels by screwing them into place.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the base frame of the rolling cart.

attributes.Transcription: Put them next to each other, so that the open part looks upwards and in the middle.

attributes.Action sentence: The student assembles the upper side bars.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should first connect the curved tubes to the other tubes.

attributes.Transcription: First, connect the curved tubes to the other tubes.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should make sure that the hole in the middle is at the bottom.

attributes.Transcription: Make sure that the hole in the middle is at the bottom.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should assemble the frame first.

attributes.Transcription: Now take the other tubes and put them on the top.

attributes.Action Correctness: Wrong Action, corrected by instructor verbally
attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should make sure that the top bends inwards.

attributes.Transcription: Make sure that the top bends inwards.

attributes.Action sentence: The student places the biggest grid tray at the bottom.

The student screws the right side of the top tray.

attributes.Transcription: Put the second biggest tray at the bottom for now and just attach the top tray.
If you have any trouble screwing it on, you can also put the whole thing to its side.

attributes.Action sentence: The student aligns the tray in the middle.
The student screws the left side of the bottom tray.
